Dear Adi,

I see your points but I disagree.

A gene list is always derived from somewhere. Thus, there are particular 
experiments associated with it. Under this particular experimental setting, 
there are stereotypes of UP and DOWN. With that being said, we can also find 
metadata associated with a gene list is important to keep.

As such, I think the directions make sense; although mathematically the sign 
can be flipped, biologists have predefined contexts of UP and DOWN.

Simon

